Text: During the past week we have steered away from further investigation into personal user stories and branched into development work.
With each members goals of the project in mind, we have each decided to begin working on development tasks which will in turn help us achieve our project goals.

This has been an important transition as without having done it we could spend far too much time collecting information and understanding the requirements of different users without meeting the actual needs the client has of updating the OPT's website.
The end of last week consisted of low fidelity mock ups on paper.

With each group member having a particular user story that was investigated, we took our ideas for what they specifically needed or would like to see on the website and actioned these requirements in the initial design.
Without spending too much time on it, I made the high fidelity mock ups through a CMS site - Square Space.
This enabled me to explore different templates and understand good design requirements.
Ruru also sought out examples of websites which have a good design and shared them with us which helped inform the final design.
Throughout the week I worked on the high fidelity mock up, seeking images to use, content to transfer into the new landing page and prioritizing our users we identified.
With this being achieved by the end of the week, WordPress developer being installed and the group being in mutual agreement that the design was completed, the technical work has begun.
One of the challenges this week has been installing XAMPP and WordPress developer.
It is no longer a surprise to me that installing the software packages require is one thing, but setting it up properly and getting it to work is a challenge on its own.
This cost my team a lot of patience.
Doing it however was a barrier to entry in itself and therefore worth the time spent installing it properly as well as researching the functionalities it has and how to use them.
This next week I will continue build the landing page in order to achieve my goal of making a website.
I will achieve this by following the design which has been made and using internet resources which teach me about the tools and functionality that can be used on WordPress.
